<br>
For many, EQ is not a &quot;game.&quot;  When kids used to say that about Dungeons and Dragons, it was time for the psychologist.  But it's just not like that here.  It goes way past dungeons OR dragons in much of Norrath - it's about real people.<br>
<br>
I'm glad EQ is not so much a real RPG.  I have met some wonderful, real, living people -- not stereotypical characters.<br>
<br>
How fortunate those who knew Morrigu in Norrath were to have known her.<br>
<br>
And how much the better are we all that we know each other who are still here?  I have faith that we are the better for it.<br>
<br>
Your time in Norath was not wasted, Margaret Peggy Danforth.  Those who knew you as Morrigu will always remember how you touched their lives, and they will be glad of the memory... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc>News Bulletin</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
